SECTION 1: PHYSICS RATIONALE
--------------------------------------------------

  120-cell / 600-cell duality:
    120-cell: 120 dodecahedral cells.  Dual: 600-cell (600 tetrahedral).
    M8G uses the 120-cell: 120 layers, 720 vias, k_c(H4) = 3.183.

  H3 projection of 600-cell:
    Project 600-cell to 3D under icosahedral symmetry (H3 Coxeter group).
    The icosahedron emerges: 12 vertices, 30 edges, 20 triangular faces.
    Via positions: 30 edge midpoints per layer.
    Layer structure: 24 layers x 15 deg rotation = 360 deg (full).
    Total vias: 24 x 30 = 720  (same count as M8G).

  k_c(H3) ~ 2.13:
    H3 Coxeter data: exponents {1, 5, 9}, Coxeter number h=10, |W|=120.
    Bost-Connes KMS critical point for H3 ~ 2.13.
    (H4: exponents {1,11,19,29}, h=30, |W|=14400, k_c=3.183.)
    Formal derivation pending (M22-H3). Value from 600-cell projection.

  Layer pitch: 0.1mm  (Rogers 4350B, 0.1mm core, Dk=3.48, Df=0.0037)
  Total board: 2.4mm  (24 x 0.1mm)
  Cost: ~$400  (vs M8G ~$3000)

SECTION 2: CORE NUMBERS
--------------------------------------------------

  phi (golden ratio) = 1.61803398875
  alpha_0 = 299 + pi/10 = 299.314159265
  f_res = 299.314159 MHz  (M1 certified)

  k_c(H4) = 3.183  (120-cell, M8G)
  k_c(H3) = 2.13  (icosahedron, M8E -- DIFFERENT)
  Ratio k_c(H4)/k_c(H3) = 1.4943662

  Layers:      24  (= 120/5, 5-fold reduction)
  Rotation:    15.0 deg/layer  (= 360/24)
  Vias/layer:  30  (icosahedral edge midpoints)
  Total vias:  720  (same as M8G)
  Layer pitch: 0.1 mm
  Total thick: 2.4 mm

SECTION 3: H3 COXETER DATA
--------------------------------------------------

  Coxeter group H3 (full icosahedral symmetry group):
    Exponents m_i: {1, 5, 9}
    Coxeter number h = 10
    Rank n = 3  (3-dimensional)
    Order |W(H3)| = 120
    Number of positive roots: h*n/2 = 10*3/2 = 15
    Diagram: o---o===o  (the === is a 5-edge, giving 5-fold symmetry)

  Comparison with H4 (120-cell):
    H4 exponents: {1, 11, 19, 29}  h=30  n=4  |W|=14400
    H3 is the maximal 3D Coxeter subgroup of H4.
    H3 < H4 as subgroups: |W(H4)|/|W(H3)| = 14400/120 = 120.
    This ratio 120 = number of layers in M8G.

  H3 angular signature at via centres:
     60 deg x2  (equilateral triangle, icosahedron faces)
    108 deg x2  (pentagon interior angle -- H3 signature)
    144 deg x2  (golden gnomic pairs)
    Total: C(4,2) = 6 pairs per via, 30 x 6 = 180 checks
    MAX_DEVIATION: 0.000000 deg  (certified by 24cell_vertices.py)

