SECTION 5: GATE STRUCTURE (7/8 PASS REQUIRED)
--------------------------------------------------

  REQUIRED GATES (C01-C07) -- all must pass to fab:
  C01: CSV geometry valid
       720 vias, 24 layers, 30/layer
  C02: H3 symmetry per layer
       angles {60, 108, 144} deg, tol 0.01 deg
  C03: Layer count = 24
       not 120 -- H3 pre-test
  C04: Via count = 720 (24x30)
       same count as M8G
  C05: f_res = 299.314 MHz
       M1 certified
  C06: k_c(H3) = 2.13 +/- 0.10
       H3 BC cliff (H4 = 3.183)
  C07: Cliff at correct voltage
       2.13 V +/- 0.15 V

  OPTIONAL GATE (C08) -- can fail; 7/8 is sufficient:
  C08: Via drill tolerance <= 20 um
       (M8G requires 5 um; 24-layer board tolerates 20 um)

  IF C07 FAILS (cliff at wrong voltage) and C01-C06 pass:
    -> k_c(H3) prediction is wrong
    -> Recheck M8C gear ratio (gear = 3/6 may be incorrect)
    -> Do NOT build M8G until M8C is fixed

